          <h1 id="project-title">The Minion Circuit</h1>

      <p>The Minion Circuit is a project that aims to take a first step to teaching younger audiences the difference between an opened and closed circuit. When the user holds hands with the minion plush toy, the LED embedded inside the minion lights up; hence the closed circuit. Once the hands of the minion are let go, the LED is no longer lit; hence the opened circuit.

 

      As an electrical engineer and emerging creative technologist, I worked with Yining Shi on The Minion Project.

      My role in this project involved circuit fabrication, UX/UI on The Minion Project website and backend sockets connection coding.</p>



      <p>DEM Tales is an interactive, animated, STEM enriched mobile platform. DEM Tales is a call-to-action project to support and provide an alternative curriculum to underserved NYC students.</p>



      <p>DEM Tales contains a collection of animated episodes. These episodes present STEM content in a mixture of popular colloquialisms and interaction. Users are held accountable if they wish to reach the conclusions of each episode. For example, if the user is watching an episode, it will pause at a certain point. The user will be prompted to drag and drag an item to a designated portion on the screen. The episode will not continue until this action is performed.</p>

